newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 1,485 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 1,485 contracts.

text.p: The Chicago Board of Trade Project A overnight agricultural trading volume totalled 1,485 contracts compared with 1,517 overnight Tuesday, according to the CBOT.
There were 108 wheat, 409 corn, 832 soybean, 100 soymeal, and 36 soyoil contracts traded. Two corn puts and three soybean calls were traded.
In overnight trading, wheat was two to 1-1/4 cents per bushel higher, corn was 1/4 cent lower to one cent higher and soybeans were 2-3/4 to 6-1/2 cents higher.
